Asserts soundness of the abstract-domain union (lattice join) on
What4's wraparound-aware arithmetic interval domain: for any x in
either input domain, x is also in the union.

A 'Dom n' is either bottom or an interval { lo, sz } whose
membership predicate wraps modulo 2^n: x in Dom iff x - lo <= sz.
The union picks endpoint representatives in [n+2] so the midpoints
of the two intervals fit within 2^(n-1) of each other, then takes
the bounding interval of the four endpoints. The construction is
subtle because of the wraparound behavior.

The k = 32 variant operates on k-bit intervals.
